This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes an efficient neural architecture search approach for multi-attribute learning. Additionally, the paper also involves experiments on benchmark datasets, which further supports its classification under cs.LG. 

The paper also involves computer vision tasks, such as multi-attribute learning, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision). 

Furthermore, the paper involves the use of deep learning techniques, which could classify it under the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

The paper also involves natural language processing tasks, such as encoding attribute-specific features, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). 

Finally, the paper involves experiments on multi-media datasets, which suggests that it could also belong to the sub-category of cs.MM (Multimedia).
